Implementation summary:
- `CoreIpcOptions` (sealed record with init-only properties) defines all default
  parameters mandated by design.md §"CoreIpcConfigLoader":
    Host=127.0.0.1, Port=61874, DefaultRequestTimeout=5s,
    ReconnectInitialDelay=250ms, ReconnectMultiplier=2.0,
    ReconnectMaxDelay=5s, ReconnectMaxAttempts=20,
    MaxMessageSizeBytes=1_048_576, EventQueueWarningThresholdPerTopic=1000,
    LogLevel=Info. The accompanying `LogLevel` enum exposes 5 levels
    (Trace, Debug, Info, Warning, Error) per Req 7.4.
- `CoreIpcError` is an abstract record carrying (Code, Message). Nine sealed
  variants implement the discriminated union per design.md §"Error Strategy":
    NotConnected, SizeLimitExceeded(actual, limit), InvalidTopic(topic),
    InvalidEnvelope(reason), RequestTimeout(elapsed), PortInUse(port),
    ProtocolVersionMismatch(received, expected), TransportFailure(details),
    HandlerException(details). Stable codes (NOT_CONNECTED, SIZE_LIMIT, ...)
    are preserved for log/diagnostic correlation.
- `IpcResult` and `IpcResult<T>` are immutable readonly structs that expose
  `Ok` / `Fail` factories and equality semantics. Generic `Fail` returns
  default value, non-generic `Fail` rejects null errors via ArgumentNullException.
- `IsExternalInit` shim is added so init-only properties / records compile
  cleanly under the Unity 6.3 / .NET Standard 2.1 target without the BCL
  shipping `System.Runtime.CompilerServices.IsExternalInit`.

Tests added (NUnit, EditMode, Tests/Editor):
- `CoreIpcOptionsDefaultsTests`
    DefaultInstance_ExposesContractDefaults — observable completion criterion:
      Host=127.0.0.1, Port=61874, DefaultRequestTimeout=5s,
      MaxMessageSizeBytes=1_048_576.
    DefaultInstance_ExposesReconnectAndLoggingDefaults — verifies all reconnect
      defaults + EventQueueWarningThresholdPerTopic=1000 + LogLevel=Info.
    With_PartialOverride_PreservesOtherDefaults — `with`-style init pattern
      keeps other defaults intact.
- `CoreIpcErrorVariantsTests`
    AllVariants_AreSubtypesOfCoreIpcError_AndCarryStableCodes — covers all 9
      variants and the 9 expected codes.
    SizeLimitExceeded_PreservesActualAndLimit, RequestTimeout_PreservesElapsed,
    Records_WithSamePayload_AreEqual — verify record equality / payload
      preservation.
- `IpcResultTests`
    Ok / Fail behaviour for both `IpcResult` and `IpcResult<T>`,
    null-error guard for `IpcResult.Fail`, and default-value behaviour for
    `IpcResult<T>.Fail`.

